@node intro "Introduction"
This program retrieves local meterological data from the Internet, and saves it in (regulary updating) env-vars to allow you to display it in the WB titlebar.  It can also report conditions in its own GUI, display an icon on Workbench with customisable title, and/or in AmiDock.  Trend forecasts for the next hour are displayed if available, and full forecast support for ~24 hours can also be requested.

Why "Wet"?  Well, because that's "lovely weather for ducks".  And ducks sounds (a bit) like dockies, which is what it was intended to be originally (this was seriously put on hold and later resurfaced as an additional feature).  It was also going to be a shared library, that's more-or-less been shelved, but may return in the form of plug-in decoder modules for Wet at some point in the future.
@endnode

@node install "Installation and initial setup"
@{b}It is highly recommended to remove any currently running versions of Wet using Commodities Exchange, before running through the installation.@{ub}

Run the Install script. (you can also set up manually - if you do this be aware that you @{u}must@{uu} point the DATA tooltype to the location the data files and icons are installed in)

@{b}Initial Setup@{ub}
Start the program once (or twice if it does not appear on the first attempt), and click on the Location tab.

You can either type an ICAO code in directly if you know it, or more useful for most people there is a find option detailed below:

Set the latitude and longitude gadgets at the top of the window to your physical location.

Try one of these sites to find your co-ordinates:
@{u}http://www.maporama.com/@{uu}
Bottom-left, just underneath the weather information. :)

@{u}http://space.cweb.nl/phplocos.html@{uu}
Shows latitude/longitude in decimal initially, but clicking on it will give the required degrees, minutes and seconds notation.

@{u}http://www.streetmap.co.uk@{uu} (UK only)
Click on "convert coordinates".

Now click on Find within Wet.  After a few seconds, a requester will appear showing you the nearest site name and approximately how far away it is (in miles or kilometres depending on your locale settings).  Wet will also try to obtain the current weather automatically, and tell you if there is no data available, in which case you can select an alternative site from the pop-up gadget next to the Find button.

An alternative method is to choose the menu item "Project->Execute ARexx..." and select the search_nsd.wet script.  You can then type in the name of your nearest airport and a list of potential codes will be displayed.  UK-based users might find ukpostcode.wet more convenient.

Clicking "Save" at this point will write the settings to tooltypes.  Closing the window will hide Wet.

Please refer to the following sections to configure Wet to show the weather in your preferred format on the Workbench screen.
@endnode

@node titlebar "Weather in the WB titlebar"
The following steps will allow you to add statistics to the WB titlebar.

Open up Workbench prefs, and click "Insert" under "Screen Title Format". Select "Env variable", and type in one of the following:

weather/temp
weather/pressure
weather/wind
weather/windspeed
weather/winddirection
weather/visibility
weather/dewpoint
weather/weather
weather/observationtime
weather/cloudcover
weather/cloudheight
weather/humidity
weather/windchill
weather/maintenance (see below)

Click "Insert" and the code will be added to the WB titlebar.  Repeat for any other variables you want to display.  Save or Use your Workbench prefs and when the titlebar next updates (usually ~5 seconds) the weather information will appear.

Please note you can enclose the above variables in double quotes if you have problems with them not being recognised.

weather/maintenance contains "(!)" if the station needs maintenance.  This is to allow you to add a visible indication that the weather data may be incorrect, in line with the automatic addition of this symbol to the GUI conditions and icon name.
@endnode

@node appicon "AppIcon"
When enabled using the AppIcon option in the Settings menu, an icon will appear on Workbench showing the current conditions.  When disabled, this icon will still appear if you click on the iconify gadget in the top window border.

In the default config with the included icons, the main portion of the icon will show the most significant weather condition observed.

There are up to four mini icons overlaid on top of the main icon.  These are (clockwise from top-left):

@{fg fill}Wind@{fg text} - windy conditions (beaufort scale 6 or above)

@{fg fill}Secondary condition@{fg text} - not implemented yet

@{fg fill}Cloud cover@{fg text} - sun, sun+cloud, cloud, 2 clouds.  The "sun" icon is not shown when the big icon is indicating sunny conditions.
There is an alternative icon in the "icons" directory called "Clear".  This can be renamed to "0" and replace the "0" and "2" icons if you prefer to have a blank icon with mini sun and cloud indicators.

@{fg fill}Intensity@{fg text} - from one block to four, where one indicates the phenomena is not occuring at the point of observation, and four indicates heavy conditions.  This is not displayed if there are no prevalent conditions, or the current conditions do not specify an intensity.

Please note the overlays do not work with PNG icons, and are automatically disabled if PowerIcons is detected.  You can force Wet to attempt overlay by adding "ICONS=COLOR" to the tooltypes, eg. if you have PowerIcons installed but are using palette mapped ColorIcons for Wet's AppIcon. 

If you want to replace the default icon set with your own one, please read @{"icon naming" link icons}.

The following actions can be performed on the icon by selecting it followed by the appropriate item in the Icons menu:

@{b}Open@{ub}
Shows the main Wet window.  Same as double-clicking on the icon.

@{b}Rename@{ub}
Allows you to change the name of the icon, including inserting values.  It is valid to leave the name completely blank if you don't want any text below the icon.  Please note that the indicator "(!)" will be automatically added to the icon name if the station needs maintenance, to show that information may be incorrect.

@{b}Information@{ub}
Information on the icon.  Currently just displays the site name and sunrise/sunset times of the location the icon is showing information for.

@{b}Snapshot@{ub}
Snapshots the icon.

@{b}Unsnapshot@{ub}
Unsnapshots the icon.

@{b}Leave Out@{ub}
Only available when the AppIcon has been shown due to iconification.  This will leave the icon permanently on the backdrop (or at least until Wet is quit or the icon is put away)

@{b}Put Away@{ub}
Removes the AppIcon.  To retrieve it, select AppIcon from the Settings menu within Wet.

@{b}Delete@{ub}
Quits Wet.

All changes made to the icon are used for the @{i}current session only@{ui}, but can be made permanent by choosing Settings=>Save Settings within the main Wet GUI.
@endnode

@node docky "Docky Icon"
The icon itself is the same as described in the section about the @{"AppIcon" link appicon}.

The context menu items are as follows:

@{b}New document@{ub}
Not implemented.

@{b}Open preferences...@{ub}
Font selection for overlay text

@{b}Hide/Unhide@{ub}
Shows or hides Wet's main window.

@{b}Quit@{ub}
Quits Wet.

The docky has some limitations:

The title of the icon is not customisable.  Currently it is hard-coded to "Weather" (or localised equivalent).  This means that text-only docks will not show anything of use for Wet.

Text can be overlaid on the icon.  The font is customisable through the "Open Prefs" menu item, the colour is currently hard-coded to black, and the text to display is the same as the AppIcon title - this can be changed by enabling the AppIcon and choosing Icons->Rename, or manually through the APPICONNAME tooltype.  This defaults to the current temperature.  If the text won't fit on the icon, it won't be displayed at all.  Bitmapped fonts should provide the best results, as the text is not anti-aliased.

To my knowledge, application dockies always appear as the last icon in the first dock.  You can move it around, but there is no way of remembering the position, and it will revert back the next time Wet is closed and re-run.
@endnode

@node usage "Usage"
See @{"Installation" link install} for initial setup guide.

@{b}Weather tab@{ub}

This shows the current weather conditions as observed at the date and time specified in the top-right gadget (this time is local, Wet will attempt to adjust for DST if Facts is also running).  Be alarmed if this is more than 24 hours behind.  There are some sites which do not send data very often, and there are others that are broken and have not updated for days, months or even years.  Occasionally stations will indicate they need maintenance.  Wet displays this as "(!)" at the end of the conditions, to show that information obtained may be incorrect or incomplete.

The units used here can be modified with the cycle gadgets to the right of the data.  These units will also be used in the env-vars/icon, and will be saved along with the config.  The humidity gadget is slightly different to the others as it changes between relative (%), absolute (g/mł) and specific (g/kg) humidity.

You can reset the units to either OS or server defaults by using the pull-down menu Settings=>Presets items.  Note that depending on current conditions, "server defaults" may not be available for all items.

The Update button will retrieve the latest information from the server and update the display and the environmental variables.

@{b}Forecast tab@{ub}

The top portion of this tab shows a trend forecast (next ~1 hour) for the current location, if available.  Sites within the US and the majority of sites outside the US do not send this information.

Underneath is a listview with an update button positioned below.  Clicking update will try and obtain a longer range forecast - usually up to one day in advance.

@{b}Location tab@{ub}

Here you set your location - see @{"installation" link install} for details.

The Save button saves the entire config, not just the location settings, and @{u}always saves to Wet's program icon@{uu}, even when launched from a project icon.  Menu item Settings => Save Settings does the same thing.

@{b}Project Menu@{ub}

There is an option "Save as" in the Project menu.  This saves a project icon containing tooltypes for the current location and icon config, and allows you to have Wet running for more than one location at a time.

The item "Remarks" gives some information about the current weather report, including any remarks that Wet has not decoded (often these are human-readable and contain further information).


@{b}Settings Menu@{ub}

The settings menu has some additional options:

@{fg fill}Suppress Warnings@{fg text} - this will stop Wet displaying error requesters during update tasks.  This is useful if you don't want to know when the network is down, or you are on a dial-up connection.

@{fg fill}Use Compass Points@{fg text} - this makes Wet show directions as compass points (16 points) instead of degrees.

@{fg fill}AppIcon@{fg text} - toggles the AppIcon on and off.  See @{"AppIcon" link appicon}

@{fg fill}Docky icon@{fg text} - toggles the docky icon on and off.  See @{"Docky" link docky}
@endnode

@node tooltypes "Tooltypes"
This only deals with "public" tooltypes that are not settable from the GUI.

@{b}STARTUPDELAY@{ub} = n
Delays Wet's startup by n seconds.  Can be used as an alternative to DELAY, but intended to workaround the docky icon not displaying with OS4.1u1.

@{b}DELAY@{ub} = n
Delays the first update by n seconds.  Useful if you use DHCP and the network is not ready by the time Wet starts.  A value of 0 means Wet will not try to obtain the weather until Update is manually clicked. (default = 1)

@{b}POLL@{ub} = n
Sets the time between automatic updates to n*10 minutes.  A value of 0 means that Wet will only update when the Update button is manually clicked. (default = 3)

@{b}PROXY@{ub} = text
Sets the proxy server to that specified.  Note that any http:// prefix must not be added, and the port must not be tacked on to the end with a colon.  If this tooltype is specified, even if blank, proxy server support will be enabled, so please ensure the line does not appear or is commented out if you do not wish to use a proxy server. (default = no proxy)

@{b}PROXYPORT@{ub} = n
Sets the TCP/IP port used by the proxy. (default = 8080)

@{b}ENVPATH@{ub} = text
Sets the environment variable path to that specified by "text".  The initial "ENV:" is not required and should not be added, additionally you should not add directory separators unless the directory already exists.   Default is "Weather".

@{b}AUTORUNAREXX@{ub} = text
Specifies an ARexx script to run after each data collection.  There is an example script wet_log.rexx which creates a log file.

@{b}NODOCKYTEXT@{ub}
Stops Wet from overlaying text on the docky icon.  Currently does nothing.

@{b}OLDWINDCHILL@{ub}
If set, Wet will use the old (Steadman) wind chill algorithm rather than the new (JAG/TI) standard one.

@{b}HUMIDEX@{ub}
Tells Wet to use the Canadian Humidex instead of Heat Index.

@{b}OVERLAYTRANS@{ub} = <1-255>
Set the transparency of 256-colour overlay icons.  This has no effect with 32-bit overlays.

@{b}THEME@{ub} = text
Sets the icon theme directory within the data directory.  eg "icons" will get the icons from <datapath>/icons

@{b}CX_POPUP@{ub} = YES|NO
Specifies whether Wet's window should show on startup or not.

@{b}NOTIFYDISABLE@{ub} (OS4.1u1 only)
Setting this tooltype disables notifications via Ringhio.

@{b}NOTIFYTITLE@{ub} (OS4.1u1 only)
Title string for notifications.  Defaults to %site%, %country%
The format is the same as for AppIcon=>Rename

@{b}NOTIFYTEXT@{ub} (OS4.1u1 only)
Text string for notifications.  Defaults to %weather%, %temp%
The format is the same as for AppIcon=>Rename

@{b}USEPLUGIN@{ub} = text
Set Wet to use a plugin instead of the internal fetcher/decoder.
See @{"plugins" link plugins}
@endnode

@node history "History"
6.1 (21.12.2010)
* Added @{"plugin" link plugins} support.
* Added hurricane categories (Saffir-Simpson scale).
* Added support for three digit wind speeds.
* Added @{"moon phase icon" link icons} support.  Large night-time icons can be appended with the moon phase 0-7 (eg. 0_n6), and mini icons mini/moon/<phase> can also be displayed.
* Added new icon set by Frank Ruthe (cha05e90).
* Wet will now pick the banner up from the theme dir if present.
* Fixed Ringhio notifications with non-English languages.
* Fixed issue with showers showing as "small hail" on Ringhio notifications.
* Fixed AUTORUNAREXX tooltype getting obliterated when saving configuration.
* Time on forecasts is now corrected to local time.

5.5 (05.02.2010)
* Compiled without optimisations for OS4 - fixes crash under OS4.1u1.
* Added STARTUPDELAY to work around an AmiDock bug in OS4.1u1.
* Added notifications. (see @{"tooltypes" link tooltypes})
* TCP/IP code fixes to fix outstanding issues and potential issues.
* Tweaked the install slightly for new installs under OS4.1u1.

5.4 (25.01.2009)

* Added support 30-hour TAFs (support for the old style has been removed).  This means the Forecast page now works again, and the simplified code should make the decoding more reliable.
* DST adjustment now uses timezone.library on OS4

5.3 (24.03.2008)

* The icon for showers was potentially getting priority over other events (eg. Snow Showers may have shown the icon for Showers instead of Snow).
* Certain sky conditions were causing crashes or no data to appear.
* NOOVERLAY=INTENSITY was errorneously present in the <wet data>/gs/0 tooltypes.
* Sunset/Sunrise times can now be set to Official, Civil, Nautical or Astronomical via a cycle gadget and tooltype.
* "Feels like" value is now Heat Index or Humidex for values over 27°C/80°F.
* Added @{"DEGTODEC" link rx_degtodec}, @{"REQUEST" link rx_request} and @{"HEATINDEX" link rx_heatindex} ARexx commands.
* ARexx scripts updated to use Wet's REQUEST command.
* uk-postcodes.csv file removed as it was legally dubious.  Changed ukpostcode.wet script to use data from http://www.freethepostcode.org - it scans the list using http-handler (http://www.unsatisfactorysoftware.co.uk/download.php?file=http) if available, otherwise will search a file called "currentlist" in Wet's data directory.
* AppIcon information requester now shows the current conditions.
* If the sun never sets or rises on a particular day at a particular location, the display now shows N/A instead of midnight.
* Changed SUNSET and WINDCHILL commands so they use the user's preference by default.
* Modified install script and AutoInstall so that Wet will upgrade without prompting through AmiUpdate.
* DewPoint values were being decoded when none existed (OS3.9 version only)
* Cloud conditions were incorrect in some instances (OS3.9 version only)

5.2 (05.03.2008)

* Added WINDCHILL ARexx command.
* Directional visibility decoding was causing a crash, fixed.
* Wet now unlocks the WB screen (enabling prefs changes).
* Menu checkboxes now reflect reality if you change them and close/reopen the window.
* The stack in the project icon is now forced to 32K if it is set below 32K.  Project icons included in this package have been modified to have a stack of 32K.
* NCD (No Cloud Detected) and NDV (No Directional Visibility) now recognised.
* Catalog directories now named correctly for OS3 (if you use the install script!)
* Faster 32-bit icon overlays [Bernd Gollesch].

5.1 (09.08.2007)

* Now includes AmigaOS 3.9 version - many thanks to Bernd Gollesch for the port.
* Now fully supports 32-bit icons - 256 colour icons are converted "on the fly", enabling the possibility to mix and match (old style planar icons are not supported yet).  Note that this means the OS4 version no longer works on anything less than "final update".
* New 32-bit icon set included by Ken "Ken's Icons" Lester.
* New tooltype OVERLAYTRANS to set overlay icon transparency for 256-colour overlays.
* Docky overlay text no longer works as the code needs rewriting for the new icon system.  It never worked properly anyway, so I don't think anyone will miss this feature.  It may reappear in the future.
* Icons are now in theme directories to allow easier adding and changing of icon sets.  You can select the theme with the "THEME" tooltype.  NB: You will see no icons if you don't use the installer or modify your data directory and add the THEME tooltype manually!
* ARexx: Fixed a crash when calling GETVALUE or GETUNIT when no data had been obtained yet.
* ARexx: RC wasn't being reset to 0 if a previous command failed.
* New ARexx script dec_to_deg.wet converts decimal latitudes/longitudes to the degrees, minutes and seconds that the GUI requires.
* Fixed a bug in the DST routine.
* Bumped version number to v5.  The version numbers will now only follow the AmigaOS internal numbering scheme, as the split version/release was confusing some people.

4.2 (06.04.2007)

* Fixed icon image corruption and crash when all overlays were in use.
* You can now modify where the overlay icons appear on the main icon.  This is done by adding XOFFSET and YOFFSET tooltypes to the mini icons.
* Added DEGREES, COMPASS and GRID as valid units for GETUNIT/CONVERT.  This fixes the bug where the command GETUNIT WINDDIRECTION returned nothing.
* Added new menu item Project->Remarks which gives information about the report and any remarks that Wet has not decoded (these are often human-readable).

4.17 (06.02.2007)

* Hopefully fixed the random crashes that occasionally occured during use.
* Fixed the crash on exit.
* Fixed the crash that occured if you entered a blank ICAO code.

4.16 (20.01.2007)

* The wind icons weren't working properly - fixed.
* Wet crashed if you issued an ARexx command - fixed.
* AmiUpdate support.
* Bumped copyright messages to 2007.

4.15 (02.07.2006)

* Fixed a bug causing a complete visual lock-up when the GUI opened - actually Steven Solie fixed it, and my thanks go out to him for tracking this down.  Wet now works properly on the current beta kernel.
* The longitude value was being read incorrectly from the sites file, this caused problems with the incorrect day/night icon being displayed for some locations.
* The time/date display now has a help hint, as the time occasionally gets truncated when using a large font (probably a Reaction layout bug).

4.14 (13.04.2006)

* Speeded up the retrieval code, it no longer hangs around after collecting data.  This might fix the freezing problems some people have been experiencing.
* Fixed a memory leak and a potential crash on exit.
* Wet is now properly charset-aware, so the GUI will display locale catalogs that aren't in the current system default charset.  The catalogs have been fixed to include the correct charset, please only use the included catalogs with this version of Wet - old ones are likely to display incorrect or missing characters.  The Greek catalog appears to have problems, if anybody can fix this please let me know. (thanks to Detlef Würkner)
* Fixed the docky icon context menu for Update 4's AmiDock/application.library.
* Added a new ARexx command @{"FINDICAO" link rx_findicao}.
* ARexx scripts now have the extension .wet.
* Added ukpostcode.wet ARexx script to find the closest site by postcode.  Note that the supplied data file is not in any way official and is not guaranteed to be accurate or up-to-date.
* Cleaned up compiler warnings and made a couple of fixes for bugs that only showed up under gcc4.  Wet is now compiled with gcc4.

4.13 (24.01.2006)

* Implemented the display of temperature (or other information) on the docky icon.  See the @{"docky" link docky} section for more information.
* The "Save as" option was causing a hard freeze.  Fixed.
* Fixed a potential crash on exit.
* After receiving a 304 response from the server, Wet would start requesting at 30s intervals.  Fixed.
* Internal code optimisations (saved 10K!)

4.12 (04.12.2005)

* Shuffled the Location tab around a bit and added sunset/sunrise times.
* Added an ARexx script "search_nsd.rexx" which wil search through the site information file for a string and return some potential ICAO codes.
* In December the month was simply showing as "%".  Fixed.
* Wind gust speed was not converting to the correct unit.  Fixed.
* The parts of the forecast that are marked as low probability are now added to the forecast again.
* Added new French translation.

4.11 (26.11.2005)

* Added AUTORUNAREXX tooltype, ARexx commands to get the data's date and time and an example ARexx script which logs the observed temperatures.
* A certain connection error was causing a recoverable alert.  Fixed.
* Rewrote most of the forecast-related routines, as still having problems with bogus data appearing.  Is now greatly simplified and hopefully more reliable.
* The date of the last update could show the incorrect month in certain circumstances.  Fixed. 
* When cloud height not available, it was being reported as -11100ft.  Now shows a slightly more correct 0ft.

4.1 (20.11.2005)

* Added a docky icon. (thanks to Stefan Robl for sending me the SDK)
* Will now work behind a proxy server. (even on a direct link, specifying a web cache proxy is recommended)
* Now retrieves data with an If-Modified-Since header, significantly speeds up updates, especially if new data is not available.
* Can now set the poll interval in 10 minute increments.
* Warnings now automatically suppressed if another app requests "game mode".
* A saved project icon sometimes resulted in an incorrect ENVPATH tooltype.  Fixed.
* Forecasts generated <1hr from midnight sometimes resulted in uneventful duplicated times. Fixed.
* Rain and Snow Showers were showing the Showers icon rather than Rain or Snow.  Fixed.
* Iconified icon (AppIcon disabled) was not disappearing if the window was reopened using a method other than double-clicking on the icon.

4.0 (27.08.2005)

* Forecast tab now shows the forecasted weather for up to 24 hours.
* Displays temperature to one decimal place when more accurate information is available. (mostly US locations)
* Displays sea-level pressure to one decimal place when information is available. (mostly US locations)
* Specific Humidity (in g/kg) now selectable from the GUI.
* Added pressure and humidity options to the rename requester for the AppIcon.
* Added HUMIDITY ARexx command.
* Now checks for weather every 30 seconds if previous attempt detected network related errors (will bring the weather up more quickly if network was unavailable)
* Network related errors (the ones that can be avoided using "suppress warnings") no longer steal focus, and automatically time out after 30 seconds.
* Now updates the weather as soon as the location code changes.
* Uses newer faster DOS functions to parse the site information file, now requires OS4 update 3.
* ARexx port now has a dynamic name, so multiple instances of Wet can all be called from ARexx.
* Included an ARexx script to download the site information file nsd_cccc.txt (requires WGet)
* Warns when observing station has problems by displaying an exclamation mark after the weather/icon name.
* Displayed gibberish after program name in CX Exchange if ICAO code was not set. Fixed.
* Double-click on program icon when it was already launched but not visible did not always open the window.  Fixed.
* Icon sometimes switched to night-time before the sunset time given in icon information.  Fixed.
* Icon sometimes never switched to night-time.  Fixed.
* Low speed variable winds were not being decoded properly.  Fixed.
* Possibility that extra weather phenomena could be reported that weren't observed.  Fixed.
* Updated German, Italian, Finnish translations.

3.2 (02.07.2005)

* Some people were still getting error "unable to resolve IP address".  This is really fixed this time.
* Changed the hiding and reopening code so it internally works as it should do rather than cheating.  This fixes the bug with DepthMenu listing Wet when it isn't open, and related changes stop Wet crashing when iconified.
* Changed the iconification gadget so Wet handles this itself.  This now shows the weather AppIcon rather than a default icon, unless the AppIcon is already active.  The AppIcon will disappear when double-clicked to reopen the window, if it was only displayed due to iconification by the user.  Note that the iconification gadget, like the normal AppIcon, does not have a fall-back state.  If you iconify when <data path>/0.info is not available, the window will still close but no icon will be displayed.
* Removed ALLOWMULTIPLE tooltype and instead reworked Wet so the ICAO code is part of the Commodities application ID.  This should give more logical handling of multiple locations.
* Added a "Save as" option to the Project menu to allow easy saving of project icons for multiple locations, also added "Execute ARexx" to enable scripts to be run from within Wet.
* Added humidity and wind chill values to the GUI and env-vars.
* Added help hints to the gadgets for the viewable weather information.  This allows you to see the full field by hovering the mouse over it, rather than having to expand the window if it didn't all fit in.
* Updated German, Turkish, Italian catalogs.

3.1 (10.06.2005)

* Added DELAY @{"tooltype" link tooltypes} to delay the first check.  This is useful if you use DHCP and the network isn't available when Wet starts.
* Added ALLOWMULTIPLE @{"tooltype" link tooltypes} as a workaround for getting additional weather icons for other areas on Workbench.
* Added a little pop-up gadget listing the five nearest sites.  This should make it easier to find an alternative if the nearest site does not work or reports data infrequently.
* Added @{"ARexx" link arexx} commands UPDATE and SUNSET.
* New German catalog, updated Swedish catalog.
* The decoding routine may be slightly faster now.
* Some people were getting error "unable to resolve IP address".  Fixed.
* If the banner image was not found, Wet would give an error and then go into an infinite loop.  Fixed.
* When AppIcons were enabled and no icons were present, Wet would go into an infinite loop.  Fixed.
* Wet tried to read from a non-existant file under certain circumstances.  Fixed.
* The decoding routine would try to match NULL strings in certain circumstances.  Fixed.
* The AppIcon state was not being correctly saved to tooltypes in certain circumstances.  Fixed.

3.0 (30.05.2005)

* Added @{"AppIcon" link appicon}.
* Added @{"ARexx port" link arexx}.
* Completely rewrote the decoding engine, it is now much more robust and reliable.
* Added Beaufort Scale descriptions to GUI and ENV:Weather/Wind.
* Can now display compass directions instead of degrees.
* Site search function now works correctly at extreme longitudes.
* Preliminary forecast support, not supported by many sites - will be extended in a future release.
* Time display now also shows the date and adjusts the time to the correct timezone (but does not take into account DST yet).
* Added some more default weather descriptions, there is now one for wind above force 5 when no other conditions are occuring.
* Env-vars now update immediately with the GUI.
* Can show sunrise/sunset times for locations (via AppIcon only).
* New Norwegian catalog.  Updated catalogs for Finnish and Italian.
* Note that nsd_cccc.txt now resides in the data directory with the other files, any copy directly in LOCALE: can be deleted.

2.01 (19.03.2005)

* Stopped Wet from locking the WB screen (you can now change screenmode etc with Wet running)
* Fixed potential crash with unexpected amounts of data.
* Fixed crash on start-up when nsd_cccc.txt was not available and no ICAO code had been set.
* The installation script now copies the documentation.

2.0 (12.03.2005)

* You can now display full weather information in the GUI, and select the units you wish to display the data in.  Shows some additional information to the env-vars as well. 
* Localised for multiple languages support, default units are now based on OS Locale settings.
* Added CloudCover and CloudHeight env-vars (reports lowest level only).
* New "quiet" mode, to stop error requesters appearing.
* Latitude/Longitude values remain valid after manually typing ICAO ID, and longitudes of >99° are now selectable.
* Directional visibility is now handled and stops the indication of 9000°C etc appearing errorneously.
* GRID wind direction values are now handled internally, although Wet shows them as values in degrees - which is not necessarily incorrect.
* Inches of mercury is now displayed to 2 decimal places.
* Changed the significant weather parsing, so Wet will now display "Snow" or "Rain" instead of "Showers", unless the precipitation type is unknown.
* Wet no longer crashes when the site data file (nsd_cccc.txt) is not found.
* Fixed several occurances where Wet could fail to retrieve or decode data correctly, often resulting in a crash.
* Pretty banner and install script added.

1.3 (01.12.2004)

* Fixed a number of bugs with incorrect or no values being decoded.  If you spot any further occurances, please contact me.
* Tidied up the GUI, added requesters etc
* Added some further values (weather, dewpoint and observationtime)
* Various other changes and fixes

1.2 (21.11.2004)

* Forgot to remove some debugging code
* Fixed a bug where values were incorrect if the observation time was not known

1.1 (21.11.2004)

* First release
@endnode

@node future "Todo"
These are the most major things on my to-do list, in no particular order (although things nearer the top are likely to be implemented first).  If you want to speed along any particular feature, pledge your support by sending me an @{"email" link contact}.

Proper prefs GUI for configuration
Funkier dockies (big temperature icons, that sort of thing)
Alerts
Popup hotkey
Show a map of where the site is (generally, using something like the Locale map)
Library (for decoder - ie. the current METAR decoder becomes a library or Wet plug-in, and can be replaced by eg. a decoder which gets data from weather.com)
@endnode

@node contact "Contact Information"
Email: Chris Young <chris@unsatisfactorysoftware.co.uk>

Please contact me if you want to translate Wet, have any suggestions or want to report a bug.

When sending bug reports, please do the following:

@{b}If the program crashes or behaves unpredictably (other than incorrect values):@{ub}

* If the Grim Reaper appears, select the "Write Crashlog" button.
* If the computer freezes completely, capture some debug output via null modem cable if you can.
* In either case, and in the case of unpredictable behaviour, send me details of exactly what you were doing and (if possible) how to reproduce the problem.
* Remember to attach the debug logs (the Grim Reaper crashlog can be found in RAM:) to the email!
* If possible, "Continue" the eror in Grim Reaper and also follow the directions below.

@{b}If values are incorrect or missing:@{ub}

* @{u}Immediately@{uu} after you see the problem, select the menu option Debug => Write Debug Info (or press RAmiga-D).
* Attach the file T:wet.debug to the email, mentioning which values you believe to be incorrect.
* If the error is in the full forecast, please repeat the above selecting the two "TAF Debug" options in the debug menu.  It might be useful to rename the debug files so I know which is which.
@endnode

